data.name: label1.Text
data.value:
1. Board Setup: - The board is 8 squares long and 4 squares wide, representing the right half of a standard chessboard. - Each player has: King, Rook, Bishop, Knight, and Pawns (placed in front of these pieces). - The distance between players is still 8 squares.
2. Gameplay: - Time Limit: Each player has a limited time to make their move. If time runs out, they lose. - Pawn Sideways Move: Pawns can move one square sideways (left or right) if the square is empty, but cannot capture.
3. Piece Movement: - Pieces move as in regular chess, but only on the 4 columns closest to the player.
4. Objective: - The goal of the game is to checkmate the opponent's king, just like in regular chess.
